1
00:00:08,039 --> 00:00:08,800
Son,

2
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:10,400
are you still working overtime?

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,040
Yes, Mom.

4
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:13,640
You catch bad guys during the day

5
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:14,840
and work overtime at night.

6
00:00:14,840 --> 00:00:17,640
You might as well come back and let me find you a job.

7
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,200
Mom, if you're calling to talk about this,

8
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,240
I'm going to hang up.

9
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:23,000
Being a cop is non-negotiable.

10
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,800
Are you trying to make me mad?

11
00:00:26,920 --> 00:00:27,680
Alright, Mom.

12
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:28,540
Go to bed early.

13
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:29,580
Good night.

14
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:58,680
Judging from the business card found at the murder scene,

15
00:00:58,720 --> 00:00:59,840
could they...

16
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:18,680
I found a lead.

17
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,560
Come in.

18
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:25,000
What time is it?

19
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,560
Why are you making so much noise?

20
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:27,920
Can't it wait until tomorrow?

21
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:29,320
What's with your attitude?

22
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:29,920
This is a murder case.

23
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:31,320
I found a clue.

24
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,120
What's with your attitude?

25
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,039
You come into my house yelling,

26
00:01:33,039 --> 00:01:33,800
and ask about my attitude?

27
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:34,759
What's with your attitude?

28
00:01:34,759 --> 00:01:36,320
Why don't you check your pager?

29
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,120
I paged you so many times.

30
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,120
If you had just replied once,

31
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:39,360
I wouldn't have come to your house.

32
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,160
I was busy.

33
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:44,289
Busy with what? What could you be busy with at this hour? This is a murder...

34
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,400
You should have said so earlier.

35
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,400
Hey kiddo, I was too loud just now.

36
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,120
I'm sorry.

37
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:55,979
I startled you.

38
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:57,250
Uncle didn't...

39
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,120
You should have told me earlier.

40
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,520
If you were putting your daughter to sleep, just say so.

41
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:07,440
Tell me.

42
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,250
Did I make her angry?

43
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,800
No.

44
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:13,800
She's just a little afraid of strangers.

45
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:15,970
What were you saying? Go on.

46
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,560
See for yourself.

47
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:22,720
Chudong Crown Nightclub.

48
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,780
This is their next target.

49
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,520
Just based on these few blurry words,

50
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,400
you concluded this is their next target?

51
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,920
There was a piece of evidence at the crime scene.

52
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:30,920
It was a business card holder.

53
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,320
One card was missing from it.

54
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,560
This card holder represents Li Na's network.

55
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,120
I suspect they will use Li Na's network

56
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,920
to continue committing crimes.

57
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,730
Is this how you solve cases?

58
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,120
Isn't it too hasty?

59
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,600
Forty thousand yuan was transferred from Linda's account.

60
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,600
Cao Aiyuan immediately sent it all to her family.

61
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,920
This shows they don't have much money on hand.

62
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,920
How do you know they don't have money?

63
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,560
She also robbed a lot of money from Li Na.

64
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,120
I've checked Li Na thoroughly.

65
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,200
She had no money at all.

66
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,160
The money she earned every month

67
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,420
was all sent back home.

68
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,920
This is the only clue I have.

69
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,920
Are you going to investigate or not?

70
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,040
I used to be a garment factory worker.

71
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:26,440
I worked 12 hours a day at the loom.

72
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,560
In less than a month,

73
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,770
my hands were full of calluses.

74
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,840
The clothes I made myself,

75
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,970
I couldn't even afford a single piece.

76
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:46,880
Those clothes would be sent to Beijing, Shanghai,

77
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,640
even Hong Kong and the United States.

78
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:55,380
At that time, I was wondering,

79
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:57,840
when

80
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,610
I could go and see those places.

81
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,280
But my father died when I was little.

82
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,440
My mother...

83
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,160
I got into college,

84
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,300
but she wouldn't let me go.

85
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:17,959
She wanted me to marry

86
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,160
an old man I had only met once.

87
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,560
Because I have a brother six years younger than me,

88
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:29,880
she wanted to use my bride price to pay for his college.

89
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:34,050
I had no choice but to give up the opportunity to go to school.

90
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,040
Little sister.

91
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,840
I had no idea you had such a pitiful background.

92
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,000
Come.

93
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,570
Let me toast you.

94
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:47,680
I'll toast you too.

95
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,680
Let the three of us toast you together.

96
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,240
Bosses, you don't need to toast me.

97
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,840
I made it up.

98
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:55,560
I was joking.

99
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,840
I fooled you, didn't I?

100
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:02,120
We three grown men were almost fooled by her.

101
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,320
This little girl is really something.

102
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,760
Regardless of whether it's true or false,

103
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,240
I think she spoke very well.

104
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,040
I was really moved.

105
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:13,840
Tell me,

106
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,920
who doesn't have their own little story?

107
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:16,800
That's true.

108
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,120
We are all in the same boat.

109
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,360
It's not easy for any of us.

110
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,000
Come on, let's toast to this together. Come on.

111
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,680
Come on, sisters, let's toast to Boss Hong,

112
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:28,840
Boss Tian and Boss Zheng.

113
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,480
May their business prosper,

114
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,440
and may they come here to have fun every day.

115
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,280
Come on.

116
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:34,210
Cheers. Cheers.

117
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,840
Yes, Mr. Yu.

118
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:42,560
Go ahead. I'm working overtime at the company.

119
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:46,340
Yes, preparing materials for tomorrow's client meeting.

120
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,720
I missed your call.

121
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,440
I was eating downstairs.

122
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,240
Okay, come on up.

123
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,480
I'll be right there.

124
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,040
Going to Chudong?

125
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,920
That's nonsense.

126
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,120
Deciding to go to Chudong just based on the mark on this card holder?

127
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,160
People in Guangzhou and Shenzhen are richer.

128
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:30,360
Why don't you search everywhere there?

129
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,890
Captain Li makes sense.

130
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,880
I will search everywhere if necessary.

131
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,280
But Chudong comes first.

132
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,440
If we can't find them this time,

133
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,240
it'll be hard to find them later.

134
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,960
The arrest warrant has been issued.

135
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,520
Police across the country are on the lookout.

136
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:46,250
We're just waiting for you two.

137
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,680
Don't say that.

138
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,280
Not me, just him.

139
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:50,560
We took this case,

140
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,040
so we have to see it through to the end.

141
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,240
We have to see it through,

142
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:56,040
but I have a lot of things to take care of at home too.

143
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,820
Fine, you don't have to go.

144
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:58,480
If anything happens,

145
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,480
I'll bear the consequences myself.

146
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:02,840
When are you leaving?

147
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:03,520
Now.

148
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,480
I'll give you five days.

149
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,720
If there's no progress, come back immediately.

150
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,680
Time is tight.

151
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,320
There's no time to apply for firearms.

152
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:18,240
I'll ask the leaders for a letter of assistance.

153
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,360
You two stay safe.

154
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,920
Us? I'm going with him too?

155
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,240
You're experienced.

156
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:34,290
I'll only feel at ease if you go.

157
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:35,720
I have to say,

158
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:39,159
this kid's investigation methods are different from ours.

159
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:41,240
Maybe you really will find something.

160
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:43,800
Maybe is just a maybe.

161
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:47,240
But what about Yinuo?

162
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,040
The usual way.

163
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,240
I'll call your sister-in-law later

164
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,570
and have her stay at my place for a few days.

165
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:58,240
Yinuo's mental state is much better lately.

166
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,640
She just needs people to talk to her more

167
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,520
and chat with her.

168
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,920
Make sure to remind your sister-in-law.

169
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,640
Don't worry.

170
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,880
Yinuo is like our own child.

171
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,080
Go.

172
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,080
If anything goes wrong, I'll hold you responsible.

173
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,240
Okay.

174
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,640
Page me if you need anything.

175
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,170
Play your cards.

176
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,120
Too big.

177
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:26,320
I can beat it. Everyone has those.

178
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,720
Wait, did I let you play?

179
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,800
Why are you trying to beat it?

180
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:29,320
Pair of jokers.

181
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:31,640
Is it big or not? Say it.

182
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,370
You're back.

183
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,090
Can't beat an eight.

184
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:39,600
Do you want it or not?

185
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,450
You guys play first.

186
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,679
Don't touch my cards.

187
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,380
I found the target.

188
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,560
Is it easy to strike?

189
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,760
Good job, baby.

190
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,890
This guy is really rich.

191
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:11,320
Will you stop after this one?

192
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:14,120
If he's really that rich,

193
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,640
I'll rob him blind.

194
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:23,480
That's not what you said before.

195
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,120
Okay,

196
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:33,240
I promise you, this is the last time.

197
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,370
What about them?

198
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,960
They listen to me.

199
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,300
And I listen to you.

200
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,600
Brother.

201
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,410
I just heard them say inside

202
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:57,440
that this really is our last job.

203
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,440
We do need to change our game.

204
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:05,440
If we keep going like this, something will go wrong sooner or later.

205
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,040
You trust her too much.

206
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,770
She's your sister-in-law.

207
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,160
Brother, are you serious?

208
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:17,320
Who is she pulling a long face for every day?

209
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:19,040
She's not one of us.

210
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,440
She's just using us to make money.

211
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:20,960
Once she gets the money,

212
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:23,160
she'll kick us aside, believe it or not.

213
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,080
Kick how?

214
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:32,840
Like this.

215
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:38,920
Boss, I know... I know I was wrong.

216
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:39,760
Boss.

217
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,920
Boss, Lao San knows he was wrong.

218
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:44,360
I know I was wrong. I'll listen to you from now on.

219
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,360
I'll listen to you from now on.

220
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,840
I was wrong. I won't run my mouth again.

221
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:47,900
Brother, brother.

222
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,370
Please stop hitting me.

223
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,420
Does it still hurt?

224
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:07,840
No.

225
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,020
What do you want to eat?

226
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,200
Anything is fine.
